In order to use a configuration management tool like Puppet, the primary Confluence configuration files must not contain volatile information.  The file, {{confluence-cfg.xml}}, which is located in the confluence home directory contains 2 parts of data which should be decoupled:  license details/hashes and also the build number.

If you look at JIRA, they are properly storing both pieces of data in its database.  This is the target design.  Otherwise, if you needed a smaller step, then de-couple into a second xml file so I can puppetize the database information.  

Thanks

