Currently if users want to upgrade from an early version of Confluence to current version, they have to sift through several pages to piece together what's involved. 

It would be a huge improvement to take this off their hands and provide a table that shows *From Version* and *To Version* and outlines the steps needed in between, at a high-level, and links to the relevant docs.

E.g. to go from 3.4 or earlier, you need to follow the [Upgrading Confluence Manually|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/DOC/Upgrading+Confluence+Manually] and [upgrade to Confluence 3.5 first|https://confluence.atlassian.com/display/CONF35/Upgrading+Confluence]

